{
  "stem": "25598.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were sort of kept-- the kids were kept-- away from what's happening.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But because the atmosphere changed and because people-- the adults were whispering all the time, I knew that there was something going on.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I knew that it's not good.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it became worse and worse.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then became-- then they started with the laws of wearing the yellow star.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Prior to '38, life was absolutely wonderful.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a peaceful harmony to our life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was some kind of a flowing structure in which-- like every day was a day for a specific thing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Like the girl comes to do the wash on Mondays, and the other one comes to do the ironing on Tuesday.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the shopping day is on Thursday because we're preparing for Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then cooking is Friday-- because my mother, on Thursday, had to help my father in the store because Thursday was market day.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Every day had a specific function, and it was all good.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that the smells in the kitchen were just fantastic.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my mother was a terrific cook, and she loved to bake and to cook.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she had great parties.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And people would come, and everybody would be delighted, and people would have a wonderful time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was-- it was a beautiful life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Shabbat started Friday evening when my father came home earlier from his store.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the table-- my mom and I would set the table, and the candles, and the challah, and everything.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then, even though we had a tub in the house, and we had running water-- which not many homes in the city did-- and we had cold and hot water in the house.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
